Author: yomishino
Punchline: Compasses that detect and mark certain nearby objects/NPCs
Description:
[Important!] Please disable AND uninstall any non-preview version if you'd like to install this version.

This plugin detects certain objects/NPCs such as Aether Currents nearby and shows where they are by various ways, e.g. pointing to their locations on screen and notifying you in Chat.

Currently detects:
	- Aether Currents
	- Eureka Elementals (by apetih)
	- Mob Hunt Elite Marks
	- Gathering Points
	- [Experimental] Island Sanctuary Gathering Objects and Animals
	- [Experimental] Quest-related NPCs/Objects
	- [Experimental] Eureka Elementals (by apetih) 

Note: Because most objects/NPCs are not loaded when they are too faraway or when there are too many entities nearby (such as too many player characters), they will not be detected in this case.

Icon by Lumas Arkfrost

Description:
Analyses combat information every frame and finds the best action.

This means almost all the information available in one frame in combat, including the status of all players in the party, the status of any hostile targets, skill cooldowns, the MP and HP of characters, the location of characters, casting status of the hostile target, combo, combat duration, player level, etc.
Then, it will highlight the best action on the hot bar, or help you to click on it.
It is designed for `general combat`, not for savage or ultimate. Use it carefully.

Changelog:
1.5.0.36:
    * Flare to Flare Star added.
    * Holy to Glare IV added.
    * Primal Upheaval (Upheaval/Orogeny to Primal Wrath) added.
    
    1.5.0.35:
    * Furious Steel Fang changed into Snapping Fury, which just replaces Writhing Snap with Uncoiled Fury in general if you have stacks. It should still be enabled if you enabled it before.
    
    1.5.0.33:
    * Removed Stardiver to Nastrond. It doesn't make much sense anymore with the Nastrond changes, it's incompatible with the opener, and Stardiver to Dragonfire Dive just works better (and now follows opener order).
    
    1.5.0.27:
    * Added separate option for combo-ing Gibbet and Gallows together only in the Slice combo.
    
    1.5.0.25:
    * Three PCT additions added, very secretive.
    * PCT main combo movement feature added.
    * MNK rework. Stuff removed, stuff added. Probably should check it out yourself and redo your bars. I'd ideally just recommend not playing Monk at all in its currently abysmal state, but if you're levelling everything to 100, you'll have to eventually.
    
    1.5.0.23:
    * BRD Battle Voice/Radiant Finale/Raging Strikes priority changed to conform with new rotation.
    * Verproc into Jolt Plus Verthunder Option added so that you can always use Verfire. This is because the most optimal opener for Red Mage requires using Verfire during Acceleration.
    
    1.5.0.22:
    * Shroud only option added to Enhanced Gallows and Gibbets.
    
    1.5.0.20:
    * VPR Ouroboros Feature added now that the gauge was updated.
    
    1.5.0.19:
    * RDM's Verproc into Jolt combo now no longer gets replaced by Grand Impact outside of Jolt.
    * Fixed minor Autocrossbow into Hypercharge visual bug.
    
    1.5.0.18:
    * Swiftcast into Raise should change into Raise if abilities aren't available due to Amnesia.
    * DNC Standard Step into Last Dance added.
    * VPR Coiling Dens Swap Option added.
    * VPR Twin Tails feature added (Twinfang/blood into Serpent's Tail).
    * VPR Furious Steel Fang option for Writhing Steel Fang feature added.
    
    1.5.0.17:
    * GNB Demon Slaughter combo to Lion Heart combo added.
    * Optional Jolt opt-out features for Verfire/Verstone each for the Verproc combo added.
    * DRK Stalwart Soul to Disesteem feature should now work if you have the vanilla Living Shadow to Disesteem function disabled.
    
    1.5.0.16:
    * GNB Burst Strike/Fated Circle to Lion Heart combo (Reign of Beasts) separated from the Bloodfest feature.
    * Also just cleaned up the GNB section in general.

    1.5.0.11:
    * Blizzard 1/3 Feature now works properly.
    * High Fire 2 to Flare feature rewritten now that Enhanced Flare is gone and (High) Fire 2 is no longer used after switching to Astral Fire if you have Flare.
    * Lance Charge to Dragon Sight removed because Dragon Sight no longer exists.
    
    1.5.0.8:
    * Flare to Despair now works via reverse-AoE action detection, like Xenoglossy to Foul.
    * High Thunder to High Thunder 2 added.
    * Disclaimer added to (Between the) Ley Lines.
    * Despair to Transpose removed.
    
    1.5.0.3:
    * Initial Viper features added. More will be added later when there is further access to Job Gauge variables via Client Structs.
    
    1.5.0.1:
    * Initial Pictomancer features added.
    
    1.5.0.0:
    * Wayyy too much. Please check the commits on the github, I left changelogs for each job there.

Tired of clicking yes in Praetorium? Can't stand using keys in dungeons? Well do I have the plugin for you! Yes Already is specifically designed to click all the annoying dialogs you've grown accustomed facerolling. Just enter the dialog text, and you'll never see it again! Also works with /regex/ and has several built-in modules for dialogs that aren't quite yes/no prompts but act like it (like desynth).

Plugin from https://love.puni.sh/ment.json
Changelog: fixed salvage bulk, fixed item inspection

Author: Haselnussbomber
Name: Yo-kai Check
Description:
Yo-kai Check is a small plugin to assist you in tracking the rewards of the Yo-kai Watch event.

Plugin from https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Haselnussbomber/DalamudPlugins/main/repo.json
Punchline: Tracking assistant for Yo-kai Watch rewards
Changelog:
- Added: The server info bar entry can not be clicked to open the plugin window.
- Added: The server info bar entry now shows the locations in which you can farm the medals in the tooltip.
- Added: In the table, the medal count of each weapon now also has a tooltip that shows the locations in which you can farm them. A location displayed in a green color is your current location.
- Added: In the table, the minion name can now be clicked to summon it and will be shown in a green color when it is currently summoned.
- Changed: The server info bar entry is now based on the currently summoned minion (previously it was based on inventory changes - the medals that were added) and will persist between zones until the minion is sent away or the weapon has been acquired.
